Subject: Re: '74 Westy wheel hub question

Before you break the big hub nut off it's a good idea to mark it up so you
know where you've got to tighten it back to - I used a cold chisel to put a
little nick in it - makes it easier to line up the hole for the cotter pin.

Dan Smyth
